---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Support & Help Center — ThinkMode+" description="Get help with ThinkMode+. Find installation guides, troubleshooting tips, FAQs, and learn how to report bugs or request features." canonicalPath="/support">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="legal-page">

      <h1>Support & Help Center</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Everything you need to get up and running with ThinkMode+.</p>

      <!-- ── Getting Started ── -->
      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <p>
        Setting up ThinkMode+ takes less than a minute. Follow these steps to start getting
        better AI responses automatically:
      </p>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Install the Extension</h3>
            <p>
              Visit the <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Chrome Web Store</a>
              and search for <strong>ThinkMode+</strong>, or use the install link on our
              <a href="/">homepage</a>. Click <strong>"Add to Chrome"</strong> (or "Add to Edge"
              if you're using Microsoft Edge) and confirm the installation.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Pin the Extension</h3>
            <p>
              Click the <strong>puzzle-piece icon</strong> (Extensions) in your browser toolbar,
              find ThinkMode+, and click the <strong>pin icon</strong> next to it. This keeps
              ThinkMode+ visible in your toolbar for quick access to settings.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Configure Your Preferences</h3>
            <p>
              Click the <strong>ThinkMode+ icon</strong> in your toolbar to open the popup.
              From here you can toggle which platforms (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini) should have
              extended thinking enabled automatically. That's it — you're done!
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p>
        Once configured, ThinkMode+ works silently in the background. Every time you open a
        supported AI platform, extended thinking will already be turned on.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <!-- ── Troubleshooting ── -->
      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <p>
        If ThinkMode+ doesn't seem to be working as expected, try the following steps:
      </p>

      <div class="troubleshoot-list">
        <div class="troubleshoot-item">
          <h3>🔄 Refresh the Page</h3>
          <p>
            The simplest fix is often the most effective. Hard-refresh the AI platform page
            with <code>Ctrl + Shift + R</code> (Windows/Linux) or <code>Cmd + Shift + R</code>
            (Mac). ThinkMode+ activates on page load, so a refresh gives it a clean start.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="troubleshoot-item">
          <h3>🌐 Check You're on a Supported Platform</h3>
          <p>
            ThinkMode+ currently works on these domains:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li><code>chatgpt.com</code> — OpenAI's ChatGPT</li>
            <li><code>claude.ai</code> — Anthropic's Claude</li>
            <li><code>gemini.google.com</code> — Google's Gemini</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            If you're using a different URL (e.g., an API playground or enterprise instance),
            the extension may not activate.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="troubleshoot-item">
          <h3>🧩 Verify the Extension Is Enabled</h3>
          <p>
            Open <code>chrome://extensions</code> in your browser's address bar and make sure
            ThinkMode+ is toggled <strong>on</strong>. If it was recently updated, you may need
            to click the refresh/reload button on the extension card.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="troubleshoot-item">
          <h3>⚠️ Check for Conflicts</h3>
          <p>
            Other browser extensions that modify AI platform interfaces may conflict with
            ThinkMode+. Try temporarily disabling other extensions to see if the issue resolves.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="troubleshoot-item">
          <h3>🔄 Reinstall the Extension</h3>
          <p>
            If nothing else works, remove ThinkMode+ from <code>chrome://extensions</code> and
            reinstall it from the Chrome Web Store. This ensures you have the latest version
            with a clean state.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <!-- ── FAQ ── -->
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <p>
        We maintain a comprehensive FAQ on our homepage covering the most common questions about
        ThinkMode+ — including how it works, pricing, platform support, and privacy.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/#faq" class="faq-link">
          <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"></circle><path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 0 1 5.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"></path><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"></line></svg>
          View the full FAQ on our homepage →
        </a>
      </p>

      <hr />

      <!-- ── Reporting Bugs ── -->
      <h2>Reporting Bugs</h2>
      <p>
        Found something broken? We want to fix it. When reporting a bug, please include the
        following information so we can reproduce and resolve it as quickly as possible:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Browser and version</strong> — e.g., Chrome 130.0.6723.91 or Edge 130.0.2849.56</li>
        <li><strong>Platform affected</strong> — ChatGPT, Claude, or Gemini</li>
        <li><strong>Steps to reproduce</strong> — What you did, step by step, when you encountered the issue</li>
        <li><strong>Expected vs. actual behavior</strong> — What should have happened vs. what actually happened</li>
        <li><strong>Screenshots</strong> (optional but helpful) — Visual evidence of the problem</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Send your bug report to
        <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com?subject=ThinkMode%2B%20Bug%20Report">vypur24@gmail.com</a>
        with the subject line <strong>"ThinkMode+ Bug Report"</strong>.
      </p>

      <hr />

      <!-- ── Feature Requests ── -->
      <h2>Feature Requests</h2>
      <p>
        Have an idea for how ThinkMode+ could be even better? We love hearing from our users.
        Whether it's support for a new platform, a new configuration option, or a workflow
        improvement — we're all ears.
      </p>
      <p>
        Send your feature request to
        <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com?subject=ThinkMode%2B%20Feature%20Request">vypur24@gmail.com</a>
        with the subject line <strong>"ThinkMode+ Feature Request"</strong>. Please describe:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>What you'd like to see added or changed</li>
        <li>Why it would be useful to you</li>
        <li>Any examples or references that illustrate your idea</li>
      </ul>

      <hr />

      <!-- ── Still Need Help? ── -->
      <h2>Still Need Help?</h2>
      <p>
        If you couldn't find an answer here, don't hesitate to reach out directly. You can
        contact us through our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a> or email us at
        <a href="mailto:vypur24@gmail.com">vypur24@gmail.com</a>. We typically respond within
        <strong>48 hours</strong>.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Steps ── */
  .steps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid rgba(123, 92, 240, 0.12);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: border-color 0.25s;
  }

  .step:hover {
    border-color: rgba(123, 92, 240, 0.35);
  }

  .step-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: var(--grad);
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .step-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .step-content p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  /* ── Troubleshooting ── */
  .troubleshoot-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .troubleshoot-item {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .troubleshoot-item h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .troubleshoot-item p {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .troubleshoot-item p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .troubleshoot-item ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .troubleshoot-item li {
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }

  /* ── FAQ link ── */
  .faq-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.65rem 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(123, 92, 240, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(123, 92, 240, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--violet-light);
    transition: background 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .faq-link:hover {
    background: rgba(123, 92, 240, 0.14);
    border-color: rgba(123, 92, 240, 0.4);
    color: #c4b5fd;
  }
</style>
